description: Union home minister Amit Shah announced that 82% of the 2020 Bodo accord commitments are fulfilled, with full completion expected in two years. He highlighted the transformation of Bodoland Territorial Region from insurgency to development, and the removal of AFSPA from the entire region, emphasizing economic and social progress.
title: 82% of Bodo accord promises fulfilled, rest in 2 years: Amit Shah

description: NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore, stranded for nine months at the ISS, were greeted by an 'alien' during the arrival of the SpaceX crew. The friendly welcoming came as they prepared for their imminent return to Earth. Their extended stay was due to technical issues with their Boeing Starliner.
title: 'Alien' greets Nasa astronauts Sunita and Butch as they await return to Earth

description: The annual skiing and snowboarding championship in Auli, scheduled from March 16-19, has been postponed for the third consecutive year due to insufficient snowfall. Officials highlight the impact of limited snow, planning alternative activities. Athletes express concern over climate change affecting future events in the region.
title: Bumps at Auli: 3rd year in a row, national ski championship postponed over low snowfall

description: Police in Azamgarh, Uttar Pradesh, have booked over 200 madrassas for failing to comply with government standards. An investigation found that 219 out of 700 madrassas in the district had serious irregularities, with many granted recognition and funding without physical verification.
title: Cops: SIT found 200 Azamgarh madrassas flouted norms

description: India is accelerating the development of its fifth-generation stealth fighter jet, AMCA, to counter emerging threats from Pakistan and China. A top-level committee is working on strategies to improve efficiency and shorten production timelines, with a focus on greater private sector involvement.
title: India to step on the gas for indigenous 5th gen fighter

description: A massive crackdown on an international drug cartel by the Narcotics Control Bureau (NCB) led to the seizure of methamphetamine tablets worth Rs 100 crore in Imphal and Guwahati. Four operatives were arrested, and the drugs, originating from Moreh in Manipur, were hidden in vehicles. Home Minister Amit Shah praised the efforts towards a drug-free India.
title: Rs 100cr drugs seized in NE; Shah says 'no mercy for cartels'
Study: Western Himalayas avalanche risks up due to warming, human activities

description: Three Bihar labourers aged between 18 and 20 were killed, and another was injured in a brawl initiated by inappropriate comments about a sister of one of the attackers at a Bengaluru construction site. The suspects, Sonu and Sudheer, both from Gopalganj, are being sought by police.
title: 3 workers killed in drunken brawl in Bengaluru over abusive remarks

description: The lynching of ASI Ramcharan Gautam during a rescue operation in Madhya Pradesh's Mauganj has sparked a political uproar. Seven suspects have been arrested, but the assault has raised questions about law enforcement and led to calls for CM Mohan Yadav to relinquish the home portfolio.
title: 7 held for lynching of MP cop, hostage; CM faces Cong attack
80 years on, remains of 3 US airmen who went missing during WWII identified

description: "The rise of China as a dominant economic and strategic force adds complexity, creates competition, and hampers India's effort to be the natural leader for the Global South," Gen Dwivedi said while speaking at the fourth General Bipin Rawat Memorial Lecture in Delhi.
title: China's rise hampers India's effort to be leader of Global South: Army Chief

description: Land acquired for highway development will be returned to original owners if unused for five years, and objections to compensation are limited to three months post-announcement. The amendments to the National Highways Act aim to speed up land acquisition and reduce disputes, with a focus on transparency.
title: Govt may return land acquired for national highway if not used for 5 years

description: Police have heightened security at the tomb of Mughal emperor Aurangzeb near Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar after threats from right-wing groups wanting its demolition. Access to the tomb has been limited, with SRPF deployed and barricades set up nearby. Politicians from opposing factions are using the situation for political leverage.
title: Maha alert over stir to raze Aurangzeb tomb

description: Colaba residents have requested legislative assembly Speaker Rahul Narwekar to halt the construction of a Rs 229-crore passenger jetty and terminal building near Gateway of India. They argue the project was expedited without addressing their objections and could have severe consequences for the city. Narwekar promises to organize a meeting to address residents’ concerns and ensure transparency.
title: Mumbai residents urge MLA to 'stay' Rs 229 crore jetty near Gateway of India
Student held in UP for posting clip of namaz on university campus
US intel chief Gabbard in India for key security meeting today

description: The Bombay High Court has requested the Railway Minister to consider a Rs 5 crore settlement for Nidhi Jethmalani, who has been in a persistent vegetative state since a 2017 accident involving a Western Railway car. The court labeled it a 'rarest of rare' case given the severity of her condition.
title: Decide on Rs 5 crore for woman in vegetative state after 2017 crash: Bombay HC
Japanese tourist leads Puri beach cleanup mission, raises awareness
Sambhal mosque whitewash commences under ASI watch
Student booked for Gujarat crash was influenced by Danish film: Cops
Uttarakhand mantri who stirred row with 'pahadi' remark resigns

description: Kamala Harris has a list of specifications that she wanted her interviewers to ensure during her campaigning and one of those was the height of the chair given to her.  "Leg height no less than 15 inches; floor to top of seat height no less than 18.9 inches; arms on chairs may not be very high, arms must fall at a natural height; chairs must be firm," this was the brief from Kamala Harris' team for chairs.
title: Kamala Harris demanded chairs with leg height not less than 15 inches during interview. Here's why

description: NASA astronauts Butch Wilmore and Sunita Williams are set to return to Earth after a nine-month mission on the ISS due to spacecraft issues. Their return was made possible by SpaceX's Crew-10 mission. The new crew's arrival prompted a joyful reunion as Williams celebrated with warm embraces and dancing.
title: Sunita Williams’ joyful photos go viral as she returns after 9 months in Space

description: Those who want to leave the country can fill out a form on the app along with their photo in an 'Intent to Depart' statement to the government. The individual will have to provide biographical information, current phone number and also whether he or she has enough money to depart and a valid and unexpired passport.
title: What is CBP Home App, launched a week ago, that helped Ranjani Srinivasan flee to Canada?
'We want India, China to compete in a healthy way': PM Modi on de-escalation efforts

description: Rishi Kumar, CEO of EthosAI, supports the deportation of Ranjani Srinivasan, a Columbia PhD student who fled to Canada after her visa was revoked for alleged support of Hamas. Kumar emphasized that international students must be cautious about their actions and speech, as visa privileges can be revoked.
title: Indian-origin CEO’s message for students on Ranjani Srinivasan's deportation

description: During a conversation with Lex Fridman, PM Modi reflected on his relationship with former US President Donald Trump, citing moments of mutual respect and trust. Modi highlighted Trump's courage during the 'Howdy Modi' event and their shared nationalistic values, underscoring their strong personal connection.
title: 'When bold changes happen ...': PM Modi says Trump ‘far more prepared’ in 2nd term
'Almost irrelevant': PM Modi says UN failing to fulfil its roles
Ayodhya's Ram Janmabhoomi Trust paid Rs 400 crore tax in last 5 years

description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has issued a legal notice to South African cricketer Corbin Bosch for not honoring his commitment to the Pakistan Super League (PSL). Bosch was selected by Peshawar Zalmi but withdrew to join the Mumbai Indians in the IPL. This incident has raised concerns about player loyalty and contract enforcement between PSL and IPL commitments.
title: Corbin Bosch faces legal action from PCB for breach of PSL contract
From space to Earth: The challenges Sunita Williams will face after landing

description: Kolkata Knight Riders have faced a significant blow before IPL 2025 as their top pacer Umran Malik has been ruled out due to an injury. They have signed left-arm pacer Chetan Sakariya, who was unsold in the auction, for Rs 75 lakh as his replacement. Known for his raw pace, Umran, who represented Sunrisers Hyderabad from 2021 to 2024, was bought by Kolkata Knight Riders for Rs 75 lakh at the IPL 2025 Auction.
title: KKR suffer big blow! Umran Malik ruled out of IPL 2025
'Misinformation': PM Modi on perception that 2002 Gujarat riots were the 'biggest'

description: A federal judge blocked President Trump's attempt to deport Venezuelan immigrants using a 1798 law, citing risks of persecution. The judge’s order to return airborne flights led to a heated response from the Trump administration, accusing the judiciary of endangering public safety by supporting gang members.
title: US judge halts Trump deportation under Alien Enemies Act, turning around planes

description: The United States has launched a series of airstrikes against Houthi rebels in Yemen following attacks on American and allied shipping. Defense secretary Pete Hegseth emphasised that the strikes will continue until the Houthis cease shooting at ships and assets. President Trump and other officials have warned Iran, backing the Houthis, to halt their support.
title: US threatens 'unrelenting' strikes on Houthis until they are 'done shooting at ships'
BLA releases first visuals of Noshki attack on Pakistani army convoy

description: Congress leaders heavily criticised Prime Minister Narendra Modi for his remarks on the 2002 Gujarat riots during an interview with Lex Fridman. They accused him of deflecting responsibility and attempting to justify the violence. Modi defended his position, citing prior terrorist attacks and a peaceful period in Gujarat post-2002.
title: Congress slams PM Modi’s remarks on 2002 Gujarat riots in Lex Fridman’s podcast

description: PM Narendra Modi recounted his fasting practice during a visit to the White House. His routine of fasting, which he has followed for over 50 years, left an impression on former President Obama. Modi explained the scientific and spiritual discipline behind fasting.
title: 'Last time you were fasting': When Obama told PM Modi to 'eat twice as much’
Who is Manikarnika Dutta? Historian faces deportation from UK
Lex Fridman fasts 45 hours for PM Modi interview: ‘Wanted the right mindset’
On Russia-Ukraine war, why PM Modi said he's 'not neutral'

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi highlighted India's strong cricket record against Pakistan in international matches during the Lex Fridman podcast. He praised sports for uniting people and influencing global harmony. Modi refrained from naming the best team, citing game results as indicative. He also celebrated Diego Maradona and Lionel Messi as football icons significant to different generations.
title: 'Results speak for themselves': PM Modi hails Team India's record vs Pakistan
White House says 'multiple' Houthi leaders killed, Iran 'on notice'
PM Modi breaks silence on 2002 Gujarat riots: 'Only truth matters’

description: Columbia University PhD student Ranjani Srinivasan fled to Canada after her student visa was revoked for alleged support of Hamas. Using the CBP Home app, she self-deported after she escaped arrest by ICE agents twice. Rishi Kumar, an executive board member of the California Democratic Party, who also ran in an election, supported the visa revocation and said this should be a warning for all international students.
title: 'Remember...': Indian-origin Silicon Valley leader supports action against Ranjani Srinivasan

description: New Zealand spinner Ajaz Patel has expressed support for Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli asserting their right to decide their ODI futures. He praised their exceptional careers and emphasized their impact on the game. Patel acknowledged India's recent success in the Champions Trophy and highlighted the significance of the IPL for New Zealand players.
title: 'Rohit Sharma & Virat Kohli can decide when they want to stop'

description: A SpaceX Dragon spacecraft successfully docked with the ISS, allowing for the anticipated rescue of NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore after an unexpected nine-month stay. With Crew-10's arrival, efforts to transition responsibilities to the new crew are underway, as NASA prepares for the astronauts' return to Earth.
title: Sunita Williams homecoming mission: Crew reaches ISS - What happens next?

description: Indian research scholar Ranjani Srinivasan fled to Canada after her US student visa was unexpectedly revoked, with US authorities labeling her a 'terrorist sympathiser' supporting Hamas without evidence. Despite trying to continue her studies at Columbia University, Srinivasan faced aggressive ICE actions and termination of her enrolment, highlighting alarming immigration enforcement on political activism.
title: Knocks at the door, cat left behind: How Ranjani Srinivasan fled US last-minute after visa revocation
'Feel blessed to have gained life’s purpose from RSS': PM Modi on Lex Fridman podcast

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi shared insights about his early life, highlighting the discipline of his father, his own resourcefulness, and the challenges of growing up in poverty. Despite financial hardships, his family maintained a positive outlook, focusing on hard work and perseverance without complaints.
title: ‘People told time by his footsteps’: PM Modi opens up about his father

description: At least 13 civilians were killed, and nine injured, in strikes on Yemen’s capital city of Sanaa. At least 11 others, including four children and one woman, were killed, and 14 injured, in a strike on the northern province of Saada. The Houthis’ political bureau described the attacks as a war crime and said in a statement, “Our Yemeni armed forces are fully prepared to respond to escalation with escalation.”
title: Photos of Trump watching Yemen strike in golf attire viral

description: Shardul Thakur, unsold at the IPL auction last November, may join Lucknow Super Giants as an injury replacement for IPL 2025. He was seen training with the team and celebrating Holi, sparking speculation. Thakur has previously played for multiple IPL teams and performed well in recent domestic tournaments. Official confirmation from LSG is awaited.
title: Unsold Shardul Thakur to play for Lucknow Super Giants in IPL 2025?
'Criticism is soul of democracy': PM Modi on Lex Fridman podcast - Top quotes
India, New Zealand start FTA talks as PM Luxon lands in Delhi
‘Mann saab isn’t going anywhere’: Kejriwal shuts down rumors of Punjab CM’s exit
‘Palayan roko, naukri do’: Congress’ march targets Bihar’s job crisis

description: Karun Nair is set to play for Delhi Capitals in the upcoming IPL season after a stellar domestic performance. Nair is eager to maintain his form and contribute to the team's first IPL title. He praised Axar Patel's captaincy and looks forward to playing with KL Rahul. Nair is ready to adapt quickly and stay in rhythm.
title: 'Plan will be to replicate the past success ...': Karun Nair eyes IPL glory

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi engaged in a captivating podcast with MIT scientist Lex Fridman. They discussed Modi's journey from childhood to public life, touching upon global affairs and governance. Fridman had previously described Modi as one of the most fascinating people he has studied.
title: PM Modi's podcast with Lex Fridman out: Talks about early life, journey in Himalayas & more

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, in a podcast with Lex Fridman, discussed India's strained relationship with Pakistan, attributing it to Pakistan's state-sponsored terrorism and unfulfilled peace efforts. He also recalled past diplomatic gestures, including inviting Nawaz Sharif for his swearing-in and his surprise visit to Lahore, which were met with hostility.
title: ‘We chose peace, they chose proxy war’: PM Modi on India-Pak relations
9 months in space, just $1,148 extra? Sunita Williams's pay breakdown

description: India's Bureau of Indian Standards (BIS) has conducted raids on Amazon and Flipkart warehouses to uncover non-certified products, including toys, kitchen appliances, and electrical equipment. These efforts are part of a broader initiative to curb the distribution of substandard goods on e-commerce platforms and ensure consumer safety.
title: Amazon, Flipkart warehouses raided: Toys, Kitchen appliances, electrical equipment seized

description: Hundreds of Greenlanders protested against US President Donald Trump's plan to take control of their island. Demonstrators in Nuuk waved flags and held signs emphasizing 'Respect Greenland's sovereignty.' Greenlandic leaders, including Jens-Frederik Nielsen and outgoing Prime Minister Mute B. Egede, strongly rejected Trump's idea, calling it 'unacceptable.' Greenland's parliament also issued a joint statement opposing the annexation.
title: Greenland: Hundreds protest against Trump's takeover plans

description: A persume inspired by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan's love for Mumtaz Mahal, debuted in 1921. Housed in a stunning Baccarat bottle, this iconic fragrance has become a timeless symbol of sophistication, selling 108 bottles per hour globally.
title: Mughal queen Mumtaz inspired world’s second best-selling perfume

description: Three construction laborers died in Bengaluru during a drunken brawl while celebrating Holi. The altercation, involving a woman, occurred on the third floor of an under-construction building in Sarjapura. Two to three suspects escaped, and police have formed teams to apprehend them. Superintendent CK Baba assured imminent arrests as the investigation progresses.
title: Triple murder near Bengaluru: Drunken brawl over woman turns deadly

description: Former cricketer Aakash Chopra sees IPL 2025 as crucial for Rishabh Pant's return to India's T20I squad, playing for Lucknow Super Giants. Pant must perform strongly to shake up the competition, especially against first-choice Sanju Samson. Chopra suggests Pant should focus on strategic batting positions, with significant team changes expected before the T20 World Cup.
title: 'You don't have to compete with Samson': Ex-cricketer on Pant's return to T20I side

description: Renowned composer AR Rahman has been admitted to Apollo Hospital in Chennai after experiencing sudden discomfort. The Oscar-winning musician, who recently returned from an event in London, is currently receiving treatment. Fans and artists worldwide are expressing their support and hope for his swift recovery.
title: Music director AR Rahman hospitalised in Chennai following chest discomfort
‘10,000 Himantas can’t scare one Gaurav Gogoi’: Pawan Khera slams Assam CM

description: In Balochistan, a Pakistani military convoy was attacked by the Baloch Liberation Army, resulting in 90 army personnel deaths. The convoy comprised eight buses, with one completely destroyed. However, a Pakistani police officer confirmed five paramilitary deaths. Earlier this week, a similar attack by the BLA led the military to free hostages from a train siege in Balochistan.
title: BLA claims 90 Pakistani soldiers killed in attack on army convoy in Balochistan

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah lauded the progress of the Bodo Accord at the ABSU conference in Dotma, stating that 82% of its clauses are implemented and full implementation is expected within two years. He criticised Congress for doubting the Accord and highlighted Prime Minister Modi's dedication to Mizoram's development during his visit to Aizawl.
title: Congress made fun of Bodo accord, but it brought peace, development: Amit Shah

description: DeepSeek, a prominent Chinese AI startup, has implemented travel restrictions on key employees by seizing their passports. This move aims to prevent leaks of sensitive data, potentially including trade or state secrets, as global concerns regarding AI-based intellectual property escalate.
title: DeepSeek gets 'National Treasure in China' status: Travel ban & ... it means for top engineers

description: RJD MLA Tej Pratap Yadav was fined Rs. 4,000 for riding a scooter without a helmet during Holi celebrations in Patna. Additionally, his security constable was relieved of duty after being seen dancing in uniform, following Yadav's controversial instruction to perform a 'thumka' under threat of suspension.
title: 'Expired insurance': Tej Pratap Yadav fined for not wearing helmet

description: A devastating fire at the 'Pulse' nightclub in Kocani, North Macedonia killed at least 50 people and injured over 100. The incident occurred during a hip-hop concert with around 1,500 attendees. Authorities are investigating the fire's cause, with suspicions pointing to pyrotechnics.
title: Fire at North Macedonia nightclub kills at least 50, injures over 100

description: Rahul Gandhi accused the BJP of attacking India's core values, claiming the party favors businesspeople close to PM Modi while the country's wealth concentrates in their hands. He highlighted rising unemployment and inflation as key issues. Meanwhile, BJP criticized Gandhi for prioritizing foreign visits over his constituency responsibilities.
title: 'Idea of India being attacked': Rahul says country's wealth given to businessmen

description: Economist Raghuram Rajan contested the Trump administration's economic views, rebutting claims that high foreign demand for US Treasuries drives trade deficits. He attributed deficits to excessive domestic spending and warned that aggressive trade policies risk undermining confidence in the US dollar without resolving global imbalances.
title: 'Shock and awe approach': Raghuram Rajan criticises Trump's economic reasoning

description: A six-month-old child suffered severe burns on the face and eyes due to being hung upside down over a fire by a self-proclaimed sorcerer in Madhya Pradesh. The baby is currently receiving critical care treatment. An investigation is ongoing, and the accused is currently at large.
title: Tantrik hangs 6-month-old over fire in MP's Shivpuri, eyes damaged

description: Elon Musk, the largest shareholder of Tesla, responded positively to a Twitter post revealing the top 10 shareholders of the company, with Musk topping the list at $173 billion. Additionally, US President Donald Trump recently purchased a Tesla Model S to show his support for Musk's electric vehicle initiative.
title: Tesla investor shares Tesla's 10 Biggest shareholders, Elon Musk responds with a ...
Drunk man assumes pistol not loaded, shoots friend dead in Odisha's Cuttack

description: Amboli Police have filed an FIR against an actor after a TV actress accused him of molestation during a Holi party on March 14. The intoxicated actor allegedly groped her and forcibly smeared color on her face, despite her resistance, leading her to seek police action.
title: 'Nobody can save you': Actor 'molested' by co-star during Holi party in Mumbai

description: US Director of National Intelligence Tulsi Gabbard visits India following PM Modi's trip to the US. Modi and Gabbard discussed India-US relations, with Gabbard expressing her commitment to strengthening ties. This visit follows Modi’s meeting with President Trump after Trump's second term in office began, highlighting the continuing diplomatic engagement between the two nations.
title: US intelligence chief Tulsi Gabbard arrives in India to attend key Delhi meet

description: A low-ranking official at India's telecom regulator outsmarted Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg by opting out of Facebook's mass email campaign supporting Free Basics, which violated net neutrality principles. Ex-Facebook executive Sarah Wynn-Williams’s memoir reveals the strategy and its failure, while Meta dismisses the claims and attempts to block the book's publication.
title: When an Indian Babu beat Facebook CEO Zuckerberg by 'Jugaad'

description: Bengaluru IPS officer K Ramachandra Rao has been placed on compulsory leave following his daughter Ranya Rao's arrest for attempting to smuggle 14.2 kg of gold from Dubai. Senior police officials allegedly provided protocol services for Ranya's trips. To avoid further embarrassment amidst CBI and ED investigations, state authorities have taken this action.
title: Gold smuggling: Ranya Rao's father Ramachandra was top contender for DG-IGP post

description: A Bihar police constable, Deepak Kumar, has been removed from duty after a video showed him dancing on RJD leader Tej Pratap Yadav's orders during Holi celebrations. The incident has sparked political outcry, with opposition leaders condemning Yadav's behavior as reminiscent of RJD's past conduct.
title: Bihar cop removed after dancing to Tej Pratap Yadav’s 'dance or be suspended' order

description: SpaceX's Crew Dragon capsule successfully docked with the ISS, bringing much-needed relief to astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore after being stranded in orbit for over nine months. The Crew-10 team, consisting of astronauts from Nasa, JAXA, and Roscosmos, has arrived to replace them and take over their duties.
title: Hugs and smiles as Nasa crew reaches ISS to bring back Sunita Williams, Butch Wilmore

description: Sachin Tendulkar achieved a significant milestone 13 years ago by scoring his 100th international century during the India vs Bangladesh ODI in 2012. His century tally includes 51 in Tests and 49 in ODIs. Despite his remarkable effort, India lost the match by five wickets.
title: India celebrates 13 years of Tendulkar's 100 hundreds

description: Authorities found clothing at the beach believed to belong to missing University of Pittsburgh student Sudiksha Konanki. She vanished over a week ago during a spring break trip in Punta Cana. Surveillance footage showed her with Joshua Riibe, who is now a person of interest. The investigation continues, and Dominican officials have intensified efforts to find Konanki.
title: Missing Indian student Sudiksha's clothes found on beach chair

description: The Trump administration has cut operations for US government-funded media, placing all Voice of America staff on leave. The decision affects over 1,300 employees and has been criticized by press advocacy groups for threatening the US's role in promoting free information globally.
title: 'Voice of America' funding cut; staff on administrative leave

description: Abu Qatal, a prominent Lashkar-e-Taiba operative, also known as Faisal Nadeem, was killed by unidentified assailants in Jhelum Sindh, Pakistan. He was a significant target for Indian security agencies due to his involvement in major terrorist attacks in Jammu and Kashmir, including the Rajouri and Reasi attacks.
title: Who was Abu Qatal? Key Lashkar-e-Taiba operative killed in Pakistan

description: A federal judge halted the Trump administration's deportation of Venezuelan gang members, blocking the use of an old law for fast-tracking. The Alien Enemies Act of 1798 was invoked by Trump but faced legal challenges, leading to a temporary order stopping deportations for 14 days.
title: Trump's 18th century law for speedy deportations blocked by district judge

description: Whitewashing of Sambhal Jama Masjid began following an Allahabad high court order. The court allowed decorative lighting without structural modifications. The mosque gained attention after a local court's survey order led to unrest in November 2024. The dispute involved claims the mosque was built over an ancient temple. Clashes occurred, raising debates around the Places of Worship Act, 1991.
title: Whitewashing of Sambhal mosque begins after Allahabad high court order

description: Former Bihar minister Tej Pratap Yadav faces backlash for his "dance or be suspended" remark to a policeman during Holi celebrations. BJP leaders and retired police officers criticize the RJD leader, accusing him of disrespecting the police force and reviving the era of "Jungle Raj" in Bihar.
title: 'Dance or be suspended': Tej Pratap Yadav reacts to backlash over remark to cop

description: AR Rahman, the celebrated Indian composer, was admitted to Apollo Hospital in Chennai due to chest discomfort. Doctors performed an angioplasty, and he is under observation. The music fraternity and his fans are deeply concerned and hoping for his swift recovery.
title: Music director AR Rahman hospitalised in Chennai following chest discomfort

description: A rescue operation in MP's Mauganj district turned deadly as a mob killed a hostage, Sunny Dwivedi, and an assistant sub-inspector. The chaos erupted when villagers, believing Sunny was responsible for an earlier death, became violent after discovering he had died during captivity. Several policemen were injured during the incident.
title: Rescue mission turns deadly: ASI, hostage lynched by mob in MP

description: A SpaceX crew capsule successfully docked at the ISS, bringing in a new team to replace two Nasa astronauts who have been stranded for over nine months. Technical issues with their Boeing vehicle delayed their return, but they are now scheduled to go back to Earth on a SpaceX capsule by mid-March.
title: Sunita & Butch welcome their newly arrived replacements to space station

description: Stock market recommendations: Bajaj Broking Research recommends Piramal Pharma and PTC India for the upcoming week. Nifty is expected to remain volatile, with key support at 22,000-21,700 levels.
title: Top stocks to buy: Stock recommendations for next week

description: The Baloch Liberation Army (BLA) claimed responsibility for the execution of 214 hostages after Pakistan refused to negotiate a prisoner exchange. The mass execution included only Pakistan security personnel, contrasting with the Pak army's claim that 26 hostages were killed. The BLA also acknowledged losing 12 militants, including five suicide attackers, during the incident.
title: BLA claims mass execution of 214 Pakistan train hijack hostages

description: Canada's new Prime Minister Mark Carney has directed the defense ministry to review the F-35 fighter jet purchase agreement to ensure it is the best investment for the country. The contract, signed under Justin Trudeau's administration, involved 88 F-35s for CAD 19 billion.
title: Canada to review purchase of US-made F-35 fighter jets for 'better options'

description: Vicky Kaushal’s ‘Chhaava’ continues to perform well at the box office, collecting Rs. 8 crore on its fifth Saturday, bringing its total to Rs 554.75 Cr. The film, based on the life of Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj, has been boosted by the Holi weekend.
title: 'Chhaava' day 30: Vicky Kaushal’s film beats John Abraham’s ‘The Diplomat’

description: A top Lashkar-e-Taiba terrorist, Abu Qatal, known for his involvement in numerous attacks in Jammu and Kashmir, was shot dead by unidentified assailants in Pakistan's Jhelum Sindh. Qatal, a close aide of Hafiz Saeed, recently led proxy terror outfits PAFF and TRF to conceal activities of other terror groups.
title: Close aide of Hafiz Saeed gunned down: LeT terrorist Abu Qatal killed in Pakistan

description: At least 21 people have been killed in large-scale US military strikes on Yemen's Houthi rebels, ordered by President Trump. The attacks were a response to the Houthis' targeting of Red Sea shipping routes, with Trump warning Iran to stop supporting the Houthis.
title: 'Hell will rain down': US strikes Houthi rebels in Yemen, 21 killed

description: A massive student-led protest in Belgrade challenges President Aleksandar Vučić’s 11-year rule, accusing him of autocratic governance. The demonstrations, sparked by a deadly railway station collapse, demand honest governance and an end to corruption. Government measures to limit protest size did not deter participants.
title: Watch: Serbia sees one of the largest anti-govt protests over Vucic’s 11-year rule

description: Kannada actor Ranya Rao was caught smuggling 14.2 kg gold at Bengaluru airport. Her father, DGP Ramachandra Rao, has been sent on 'compulsory leave' to avoid embarrassment. Three central agencies are investigating, with Rao's involvement denied by Ranya, who claims she was coerced into signing documents. The central agencies might summon Rao for questioning.
title: Ranya Rao's dad, an officer of DGP rank, sent on forced leave

description: Union home minister Amit Shah gifted a guitar to seven-year-old Mizoram singing prodigy Esther Lalduhawmi Hnamte after she performed Vande Mataram in Aizawl. Shah expressed his admiration on social media, highlighting her patriotic spirit. Shah's visit also included attending the Assam Rifles' land transfer ceremony to the Mizoram government.
title: Amit Shah gifts guitar to Mizoram's 7-year-old singing sensation

description: Krishna Shekhar Rana, a former vice-chancellor and well-known academic, was arrested for impersonating the 'high commissioner' of Oman using forged letterheads and a fake diplomatic vehicle. Despite an impressive academic background and no evidence of monetary gain, Rana faced arrest when security requests exposed inconsistencies, highlighting his attempt to create an illusion of power.
title: Man who posed as Oman envoy is ex-MLA's brother, a well-known zoology professor

description: Virat Kohli says he's not playing for "achievement" anymore but for the joy and excitement; admits retirement call will be tough because of "competitive Streak"
title: Virat Kohii: 'As long as I love the game, I’ll continue'

description: Samsonite has seen a decline in its Indian market due to intense competition and aggressive discounting by rival companies VIP and Safari. This drop in sales also impacted their performance in Asia. Additionally, newer brands like Mokobara, Assembly, and Uppercase offering discounts have further increased competition in India.
title: Samsonite blames deep discounting by rivals VIP and Safari as India sales fall

description: Parts of Maharashtra, particularly Vidarbha, have been experiencing extreme heat with temperatures soaring above 40°C. Chandrapur hit 42°C, making it one of the hottest spots in India. High temperatures coupled with low humidity have been causing severe discomfort.
title: Maharashtra among hottest places in India as heat streak continues

description: Facebook-parent Meta anticipates FTC scrutiny with top executives, including CEO Mark Zuckerberg, set to testify in an antitrust trial. The FTC aims to reverse Meta's acquisition of Instagram and WhatsApp, asserting Meta's dominance in the social media industry could be unlawful.
title: Zuckerberg likely to be questioned for 7 hours in case filed during Trump's first term

description: In Kakinada, a man killed his two young sons due to fears about their future in a competitive world and then hanged himself. Financially stable, he left a note explaining his concerns. The family celebrated Holi before the tragic event occurred. The man's wife found their bodies at home after returning from the office.
title: 'Ties hands, drowns them': Father kills 2 sons, ends life over ‘kids’ bleak future'

description: A grenade attack on Amritsar's Thakur Dwara temple has led opposition leaders to demand accountability from the Punjab government. Partap Singh Bajwa called for the resignation of Chief Minister Bhagwant Mann. BJP's Tarun Chugh and Punjab Congress President Amrinder Singh Raja Warring also criticized the government's handling of security. The Shiromani Akali Dal called for a judicial inquiry.
title: Blast at Amritsar temple triggers political uproar across Punjab

description: Bobby Ryan, former NHL player, faced controversy in 2022 after being arrested for attempting to shoplift at Nashville International Airport. Struggling with alcohol addiction, Ryan publicly acknowledged his relapse. Despite his buyout ending with the Detroit Red Wings in 2024, he shifted to podcasting but later parted ways over controversial posts.
title: Former Red Wings player Bobby Ryan was once arrested after shoplifting attempt at Nashville airport

description: Shiv Sena MP Sanjay Raut claimed that deputy chief minister Eknath Shinde attempted to join the Congress, sparking controversy. Raut mentioned early morning meetings with late Congress leader Ahmed Patel, while Congress leaders denied knowledge of the matter. Shinde's party dismissed these claims, asserting Raut's statements lack importance, and the BJP emphasized state development as their priority.
title: 'Shinde wanted to join Congress': Raut claims, Sena calls it 'bhang talk'

description: Authorities in Ahmedabad demolished illegally constructed houses of six out of 14 accused involved in a mob attack at Vastral. The mob, armed with sticks and swords, vandalized vehicles and injured three people. The demolished houses were located in Amraiwadi and Khokhar localities.
title: 'Illegal' homes razed after mob wrecks havoc in Gujarat's Vastral

description: Bombay High Court permits a 26-year-old woman to medically terminate her over-35-week pregnancy due to fetal anomaly. The fetus suffers from congenital macrocephaly with severe potential complications, making it "incompatible with life." The decision follows a medical board's unanimous recommendation and aligns with the 2018 guidelines for terminations beyond 20 weeks.
title: Bombay HC allows 26-yr-old to terminate 35-week pregnancy over fetal anomaly

description: India's first frozen zoo in Darjeeling's Padmaja Naidu Himalayan Zoological Park is preserving the DNA of endangered Himalayan species using cryogenic technology. This initiative aims to ensure the long-term preservation of genetic material to aid future conservation efforts, including the possibility of assisted reproduction.
title: India’s first ‘frozen zoo’ in Darjeeling with ‘bio-banked’ genetic material
